{
  "texts": [
    "Traversal of a subprocess typically leads to the addition of a metric to the problem-specific metric pool.",
    "In multi-class prediction problems, dedicated metric pools for each class may need to be generated as relevant properties may differ from class to class.",
    "A three-dimensional (3D) SemS problem, for example, could require the simultaneous segmentation of both tubular and non-tubular structures (for example, liver vessels and tissue).",
    "These require different metrics for validation.",
    "Although this is a corner case, our framework addresses this issue in principle."
  ]
}